History of CDVI Group

CDVI has been a leader in the access control and locking industry since 1985. From the founding of the company in France, CDVI Group now employs hundreds of people across ten markets. You can find us in: Benelux, Germany, Iberica, Italy, Morocco, Nordics, North America, Poland, Sweden, Switzerland, and the United Kingdom.

CDVI commitments : quality and sustainability

Our mission is to manufacture high quality, high performance access control solutions that make people’s lives easier. We also strive to make everything ourselves. From research & development to the production of plastics, metal, and packing, we do as much as we can independently.

With CDVI, you are guaranteed a high quality, reliable solution. Every single product that leaves a CDVI factory is tested before it is packed and shipped. Every key on every keypad is pressed individually. Delivering the best possible products to our customers is our priority.

The CDVI Group recognises our environmental, social, and governance (ESG) responsibility as a global business. We support local economies across our entire production cycle. In addition, we take caring for the planet seriously. Our manufacturing processes are under constant review to ensure we’re making sustainable choices.

Since 1985, CDVI has been expanding to provide ever more access control and locking solutions tailored to its customers’ needs.
Our global presence enables us to stay close to our customers and anticipate market expectations.
Our driving force is constant innovation.
 
Yoram Benhamou  – CEO CDVI Group
